title: Grateful Dead Live at Irvine Meadows on 1987-04-17
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition CC2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Little Red Rooster, Friend Of The Devil, It's All Over Now, When Push Comes To Shove, Desolation Row, Deal

Set 2

Touch Of Gray, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> Truckin', Stella Blue-> Around & Around, Good Lovin', E: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text: Phenomenol Rec/Mix Another brilliant bootleg production by taper sage Charlie Miller.  High times at Irvine for a rare Cali mid-April sprint tour.  Jerry's vocals on the big time rebound!  By comparison, check our Jerry's "Satchmo" voice  during the April 85 Philly run.
